House Resolution 33
By: Representatives Gambill of the 15th and Scoggins of the 14th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Gordon L. Gilley; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Gordon L. Gilley has diligently and conscientiously devoted innumerable hours
3 of his time, talents, and energy toward the betterment of his community and state, as
4 evidenced dramatically by his 51 years of superlative service as part of the Boys & Girls
5 Clubs of America; and
6 WHEREAS, he currently serves as Chief Professional Officer of the Boys & Girls Clubs of
7 Bartow County, a position he has held for 35 years; and
8 WHEREAS, during his exemplary tenure with the Boys & Girls Clubs of America, he has
9 further served as part of the Training & Professional Advisory Committee, Georgia Alliance
10 Compliance Committee, Georgia Area Council Advisory Committee, and Georgia Hall of
11 Fame Advisory Committee; and
12 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentleman has given inspiration to many through his high
13 ideals, morals, and deep concern for his fellow citizens, and he possesses the vast wisdom
