14 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
15 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
16 WHEREAS, he is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
17 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
18 WHEREAS, Gordon L. Gilley has served with honor and distinction, and his vision and
19 unyielding commitment the youth of this state will be sorely missed upon the occasion of his
20 retirement; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
22 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body recognize and commend Gordon L. Gilley for his decades of
25 efficient, effective, and dedicated service to the Boys & Girls Clubs of America; congratulate
26 him upon the grand occasion of his retirement; and extend the most sincere best wishes for
27 continued health and happiness.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
30 Gordon L. Gilley.
